{"word":"ἐπισκεπτέος","slug":"ἐπισκεπτέος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐπισκεπτέος</b></el> <el>(ἐπισκεπτέος, η, ον) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:verbal Adjective'>verb. <a href='S:Adjective'>adj.</a></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to be considered</i> or <i>examined</i>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:neuter'>neut.</a> <el>ἐπισκεπτέον</el>, <i>one must consider</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>from <a href='S:ἐπισκέπτομαι'><el>ἐπισκέπτομαι</el></a>\n"}]}